28// May throw ReedSolomonException
29static bool
30RunEuclideanAlgorithm(const GenericGF& field, std::vector<int>&& rCoefs, int R, GenericGFPoly& sigma, GenericGFPoly& omega)
31{
32 GenericGFPoly r(field, std::move(rCoefs));
33 GenericGFPoly& tLast = omega;
34 GenericGFPoly& t = sigma;
35 ZX_THREAD_LOCAL GenericGFPoly q, rLast;
36
37 field.setMonomial(rLast, R, 1);
38 field.setZero(tLast);
39 field.setOne(t);
40
41 // Assume r's degree is < rLast's
42 if (r.degree() >= rLast.degree()) {
43 swap(r, rLast);
44 }
45
46 // Run Euclidean algorithm until r's degree is less than R/2
47 while (r.degree() >= R / 2) {
48 swap(tLast, t);
49 swap(rLast, r);
50
51 // Divide rLastLast by rLast, with quotient in q and remainder in r
52 if (rLast.isZero()) {
53 // Oops, Euclidean algorithm already terminated?
54 //throw ReedSolomonException("r_{i-1} was zero");
55 return false;
56 }
57
58 r.divide(rLast, q);
59
60 q.multiply(tLast);
61 q.addOrSubtract(t);
62 swap(t, q); // t = q
63
64 if (r.degree() >= rLast.degree()) {
65 throw std::runtime_error("Division algorithm failed to reduce polynomial?");
66 }
67 }
68
69 int sigmaTildeAtZero = t.coefficient(0);
70 if (sigmaTildeAtZero == 0) {
71 return false;
72 }
73
74 int inverse = field.inverse(sigmaTildeAtZero);
75 t.multiply(inverse);
76 r.multiply(inverse);
77
78 // sigma is t
79 omega = std::move(r);
80 return true;
81}

83// May throw ReedSolomonException
84static std::vector<int>
85FindErrorLocations(const GenericGF& field, const GenericGFPoly& errorLocator)
86{
87 // This is a direct application of Chien's search
88 int numErrors = errorLocator.degree();
89 std::vector<int> outLocations(numErrors);
90 if (numErrors == 1) { // shortcut
91 outLocations[0] = errorLocator.coefficient(1);
92 }
93 int e = 0;
94 for (int i = 1; i < field.size() && e < numErrors; i++) {
95 if (errorLocator.evaluateAt(i) == 0) {
96 outLocations[e] = field.inverse(i);
97 e++;
98 }
99 }
100 if (e != numErrors) {
101 //throw ReedSolomonException("Error locator degree does not match number of roots");
102 return {};
103 }
104 return outLocations;
105}
106
107static std::vector<int>
108FindErrorMagnitudes(const GenericGF& field, const GenericGFPoly& errorEvaluator, const std::vector<int>& errorLocations)
109{
110 // This is directly applying Forney's Formula
111 size_t s = errorLocations.size();
112 std::vector<int> outMagnitudes(s);
113 for (size_t i = 0; i < s; ++i) {
114 int xiInverse = field.inverse(errorLocations[i]);
115 int denominator = 1;
116 for (size_t j = 0; j < s; ++j) {
117 if (i != j) {
118 //denominator = field.multiply(denominator,
119 // GenericGF.addOrSubtract(1, field.multiply(errorLocations[j], xiInverse)));
120 // Above should work but fails on some Apple and Linux JDKs due to a Hotspot bug.
121 // Below is a funny-looking workaround from Steven Parkes
122 int term = field.multiply(errorLocations[j], xiInverse);
123 int termPlus1 = (term & 0x1) == 0 ? term | 1 : term & ~1;
124 denominator = field.multiply(denominator, termPlus1);
125 }
126 }
127 outMagnitudes[i] = field.multiply(errorEvaluator.evaluateAt(xiInverse), field.inverse(denominator));
128 if (field.generatorBase() != 0) {
129 outMagnitudes[i] = field.multiply(outMagnitudes[i], xiInverse);
130 }
131 }
132 return outMagnitudes;
133}

135
136bool
137ReedSolomonDecoder::Decode(const GenericGF& field, std::vector<int>& received, int twoS)
138{
139 GenericGFPoly poly(field, received);
140 std::vector<int> syndromeCoefficients(twoS, 0);
141 bool noError = true;
142 for (int i = 0; i < twoS; i++) {
143 int eval = poly.evaluateAt(field.exp(i + field.generatorBase()));
144 syndromeCoefficients[twoS - 1 - i] = eval;
145 if (eval != 0) {
146 noError = false;
147 }
148 }
149 if (noError) {
150 return true;
151 }
152
153 ZX_THREAD_LOCAL GenericGFPoly sigma, omega;
154
155 if (!RunEuclideanAlgorithm(field, std::move(syndromeCoefficients), twoS, sigma, omega))
156 return false;
157
158 auto errorLocations = FindErrorLocations(field, sigma);
159 if (errorLocations.empty())
160 return false;
161
162 auto errorMagnitudes = FindErrorMagnitudes(field, omega, errorLocations);
163
164 int receivedCount = Size(received);
165 for (size_t i = 0; i < errorLocations.size(); ++i) {
166 int position = receivedCount - 1 - field.log(errorLocations[i]);
167 if (position < 0)
168 return false;
169
170 received[position] = field.addOrSubtract(received[position], errorMagnitudes[i]);
171 }
172 return true;
173}
